##### MF33: COVARIANCES OF NEUTRON CROSS SECTIONS                 2628 1451
                                                                  2628 1451
In MF33, we store the covariances of most, but not all, reaction  2628 1451
channels that are given in MF3. All covariances are generated     2628 1451
with the TASMAN code [kon12], which generates TALYS runs using    2628 1451
a Monte Carlo parameter method.                                   2628 1451
For each MT-number, the information consists of:                  2628 1451
1. Covariances for MTa, Ea and MTa, Ea (variances)                2628 1451
2. Covariances for MTa, Ea and MTa, Eb (correlations for the      2628 1451
   same reaction channel between different energies)              2628 1451
3. Covariances for MTa, Ea and MTb, Ea (correlations between      2628 1451
   different reaction channels for the same energy)               2628 1451
4. Covariances for MTa, Ea and MTb, Eb (correlations between      2628 1451
   different reaction channels for different energies)            2628 1451
Classes 1 and 2 are covered by NI-type subsubsections with        2628 1451
flag LB=5, followed by a LB=8 section which contains              2628 1451
the cross section variances multiplied by 1.e-3. Next, classes 3  2628 1451
and 4 are covered by flag LB=6 to account for the different       2628 1451
energy grids that two correlating MT-sections may have. Since     2628 1451
the total correlation matrix is fully symmetric, we only need to  2628 1451
include the correlation elements between different MT-numbers     2628 1451
once, and we do that in the subsection with the lowest of the     2628 1451
two MT-numbers. We include covariance information for all the     2628 1451
total cross sections, the lumped partial cross sections and the   2628 1451
individual inelastic cross sections per level (MT51,...). We do   2628 1451
not include covariances for MT600 and higher MT-numbers. For the  2628 1451
most important channels, we include cross-channel correlations.   2628 1451
                                                                  2628 1451
##### MF34: COVARIANCES OF ANGULAR DISTRIBUTIONS                  2628 1451
                                                                  2628 1451
In MF34, we store the covariances of the elastic scattering       2628 1451
angular distributions that are given in MF4/MT2. All covariances  2628 1451
are generated with the TASMAN code [kon12], which generates       2628 1451
TALYS runs using a Monte Carlo parameter method. The tables are   2628 1451
restricted to MT2 and contain covariances for the first 6         2628 1451
Legendre coefficients. Both intra- and inter-correlations of the  2628 1451
various Legendre coefficients are given. As in MF33, the LB5      2628 1451
representation is used.                                           2628 1451
                                                                  2628 1451
##### MF40: COVARIANCES OF ISOMER PRODUCTION                      2628 1451
                                                                  2628 1451
For covariances of ground state and isomeric cross sections, the  2628 1451
same procedures as for MF33 are used.                             2628 1451
